==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2023. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
{{Quote|Whole world around you, Matty, and it is friggin' huge. And all you need... are the guts to let it in.|Stick to [[Matt Murdock]]|Stick (episode)}}
*'''Enhanced Senses''': Born blind, Stick gained extremely accurate senses through lifelong training. His awareness could be used to perfectly navigate through complex environments and track down people with great ease. He taught this method to his student [[Matt Murdock]].
**'''Enhanced Hearing''': Stick's hearing was highly refined and allowed him to identify the people around him. His hearing, however, seemed to be somewhat less acute than Murdock's, due to Stick having to ask the latter about the exact number of men that [[Nobu Yoshioka]] had brought with him, but it is possible that he was just testing Murdock's senses. Nevertheless, his hearing was sharp enough to tell that Murdock had arrived in his location and [[Hand]] ninja were no longer using their swords despite being considerably far away. Stick was also able to hear that [[Iron Fist]]'s heart rate slowed when charging his [[Chi]].
***'''Echolocation''': Stick used his hearing to sense where objects were, allowing him to practically see in his own way, which was a skill he taught [[Matt Murdock]]. He used it to flick the top to his beer against the window, toaster, wall, then into the trash can.
**'''Enhanced Smell''': Stick's olfactory senses were highly keen, allowing him to smell quite a few things that were unnoticed by anyone else. He managed to identify a resurrected [[Elektra]] solely from her scent, and could tell a [[Karen Page|woman]] was recently in [[Matt Murdock's Apartment]].
**'''Enhanced Taste''': Stick possessed profound gustatory senses, as he was able to detect sugar grains, vanilla bean, milk from three different dairies from two states, a batch of chemicals "straight off the periodic tables" and dirt off the vendor's hand (from gardening) in his ice cream cone.
**'''Enhanced Touch''': Stick could feel the presence of those around him supposedly through vibrations and air currents, although the exact nature of his awareness is undetermined. He could predict attacks by feeling the air pressure generated from a young Murdock's punches, telling him to feel the breeze. He felt the silk sheets in [[Matt Murdock's Apartment]] just by feeling the air.
**'''Enhanced Balance''': His sense of balance had notably been improved from lifelong training. He was able to jump down from several feet, landing perfectly and without any injury, and proceed to kill the Hand ninja attacking [[Daredevil]] and [[Elektra]].
***'''Enhanced Agility''': Stick's balance granted him great agility allowing him to be quick while fighting the [[Hand]]. He even defeated [[Iron Fist]] easily with his agility. He also went toe-to-toe with [[Matt Murdock]].
***'''Enhanced Reflexes''': Similar to his agility, Stick also had incredible reflexes, going toe-to-toe with [[Matt Murdock]]. He also used his reflexes against the [[Hand]]. While traning a younger Murdock, Stick dodged his attacks while mocking him.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved by Wiki-Projects with the media released as of the end of 2023. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. -->
{{Quote|You're going to help me?"<br>"No, I'm gonna train you. How to control your gift, make it work for you... use it, and how to fight.|[[Matt Murdock]] and Stick|Stick (episode)}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Stick 4.jpg|thumb|250px|Stick fights [[Matt Murdock]]]] Stick was a peerless, formidable and experienced martial artist. Even at his advanced age, he remained an extremely dangerous warrior. Both [[Matt Murdock]] and [[Elektra]] would later become highly skilled combatants themselves under Stick's tutelage. Using his enhanced senses, Stick was constantly aware of his opponents. Most of the time, Stick used timing, and only needed a minimum amount of movement to dodge or subdue his opponents with lightning-fast reflexes. During an intense one-on-one fight with Murdock, Stick initially appeared to have the upper hand against his former student and mocked Murdock, though Stick did ultimately end up losing the fight due to his pupil's independent progress as a martial artist. He also held his own during a brief confrontation with [[Elektra]], but was again seemingly defeated before Matt interrupted it. Even when bound by handcuffs to a post, Stick easily took down both a resurrected Elektra and [[Alexandra Reid]], disarming them of their weapons with a well-coordinated headbutt and kicks. His fighting style included Wing Chun, Kali, Judo, Karate, Ninjitsu, Wushu, Muay Thai and Taekwondo.
*'''Sword Mastery''': [[File:NobuYoshioka-StabbedByStick.jpg|thumb|250px|Stick kills [[Nobu Yoshioka]] with his sword]] Stick was extremely skilled at using a sword in combat, being able to use his katana to swiftly slice off [[Aito]]'s hand before the latter could react, and decapitated [[Nobu Yoshioka]] in the same manner. He also managed to cut down multiple highly skilled [[Hand]] ninjas while saving [[Daredevil]] and [[Elektra]].
*'''Staff Mastery''': Stick was highly skilled at using sticks in combat. He trained [[Matt Murdock]] in stick fighting to impressive skills as well.
{{Quote|I put an arrow in that [[Black Sky|thing]]'s heart.|Stick to [[Matt Murdock]]|Stick (episode)}}
*'''Master Marksman''': Despite his blindness, Stick was shown to be highly skilled with a bow and a crossbow, being able to hit [[Black Sky]] with an arrow from a considerable distance, and to shoot down multiple [[Hand]] ninjas while himself being in a fast-moving car. When popping a beer, Stick was able to make the cap bounce multiple times, before it ended in the trash can.
*'''Master Tactician''': Stick was a member of the [[Chaste]] who was incredibly knowledgable and skilled with strategy. He taught [[Elektra]] and [[Matt Murdock]] everything they knew but also was not afraid to cut them off if he needed to as he left Murdock when realizing he was still soft. He devoted his life to stopping the [[Hand]] and recruited members with [[Star]]. He used Murdock to kill [[Black Sky]] which caused a fight between them despite Stick being successful. Stick also turned on Elektra eventually once learning she was sought out as the new Black Sky. He sent [[Jacques Duchamps]] after her, leading Elektra to try to kill Stick. He also turned on [[Iron Fist]] when he realized that Rand could be used by the Hand, so he knocked out [[Luke Cage]] and attempted to kill Rand.
*'''Master Physician''': Stick was extremely knowledgeable in using remedies to heal even fatal injuries, as when Elektra was seriously wounded and badly poisoned by the Hand, Stick created an unorthodox antidote out of toilet bowl cleaner, whiskey and baking soda to effectively neutralize the deadly poison that infected her bloodstream. The method, while very painful, was still effective and able relieve her of the poison and heal her wounds.
*'''Bilingualism''': Stick was fluent in his native English, as well as Japanese when interrogating [[Aito]].

